parks.name: Central Park
parks.description: Central Park is an urban park in Manhattan, New York City. It is one of the most famous parks in the world and a popular destination for both locals and tourists.

parks.name: Golden Gate Park
parks.description: Golden Gate Park is a large urban park in San Francisco, California. It offers a variety of attractions, including museums, gardens, lakes, and scenic trails.

parks.name: Hyde Park
parks.description: Hyde Park is a historic park in the heart of London. It is known for its vast green spaces, beautiful gardens, and iconic landmarks like the Serpentine lake.

parks.name: Central Park West
parks.description: Central Park West is a section of Central Park that offers stunning views of the Manhattan skyline and is home to famous attractions like the Bethesda Terrace and Bow Bridge.

parks.name: Yosemite National Park
parks.description: Yosemite National Park is a breathtaking natural wonder in California, known for its majestic waterfalls, giant sequoias, and stunning granite cliffs like El Capitan.

parks.name: Vondelpark
parks.description: Vondelpark is a popular city park in Amsterdam, Netherlands. It's an oasis of greenery in the bustling city, offering walking and cycling paths, ponds, and open-air theater.

parks.name: Stanley Park
parks.description: Stanley Park is a sprawling urban park in Vancouver, Canada, offering stunning views of the city, lush forests, and beautiful beaches along the Seawall.

parks.name: Erawan National Park
parks.description: Erawan National Park is a tropical paradise in Thailand, famous for its emerald green Erawan Waterfall, which consists of seven tiers and is ideal for hiking and swimming.

parks.name: Griffith Park
parks.description: Griffith Park is a vast urban park in Los Angeles, California. It's home to the iconic Griffith Observatory and offers panoramic views of the city and the Hollywood Sign.

parks.name: Nara Park
parks.description: Nara Park is a tranquil park in Nara, Japan, known for its friendly deer population and historic temples like Todai-ji, which houses the Great Buddha statue.
